multiple_choice_question.text: What do the vertical and horizontal directions in this figure represent?
What type of gauge theory does this specific brane configuration in Type IIA theory on R9 × S1 represent?
choices: U(k) gauge theory with N=2 supersymmetry
U(1) × SU(N) gauge theory with N=2 supersymmetry
U(k) gauge theory with N=4 supersymmetry
U(1) × SU(N) gauge theory with N=4 supersymmetry

multiple_choice_question.text: What change has been implemented in this figure compared to figure 1.6 to introduce a non-zero hypermultiplet bare mass and break N=4 supersymmetry down to N=2?
choices: Replacement of S1 × C part of the spacetime by a C bundle over S1
The partition function for the 6d SU(N) theory
The double-elliptic Seiberg-Witten prepotential for the 6d SU(N) theory
The low-energy effective action for the 6d SU(N) theory
The spectral curve for the 6d SU(N) theory
